how to change systemd target at boot time from GRUB menu ✅ (very important for rescue/debug scenarios like yours)

✅ 1. Steps from GRUB Menu
Step 1: Reboot server
At GRUB screen → select your kernel (don’t press Enter)

Step 2: Press e
👉 This opens GRUB edit mode

Step 3: Find the kernel line
Look for line starting with:
linux /vmlinuz-...

Step 4: Modify this line (VERY IMPORTANT)
At the end of that line, add:
👉 For CLI mode:
systemd.unit=multi-user.target

👉 For Rescue mode:
systemd.unit=rescue.target

👉 For Emergency mode:
systemd.unit=emergency.target


✅ Example full kernel line
linux /vmlinuz-5.x.x root=/dev/sda1 ro crashkernel=1G systemd.unit=multi-user.target

(You already mentioned crashkernel present — it's fine ✅)

Step 5: Boot with changes
Press:
Ctrl + X
OR
F10

✅ 2. What This Does

Overrides default target only for that boot
Very useful for:

fixing broken GUI
troubleshooting services
recovering system (like your kernel panic case)

✅ 3. Important Notes
✔ This is TEMPORARY (only current boot)
✔ Does NOT change default target permanently
✔ Perfect for rescue/debug mode

